        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is DeepCrawl better than Screaming Frog?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "For sites under 500k URLs: Screaming Frog ($259/yr) is the better tool — cheaper, faster, runs on your machine. For sites over 1M URLs, JavaScript-heavy SPAs, or teams needing continuous cloud-based monitoring: DeepCrawl wins because Screaming Frog hits memory walls." }},
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "What is the difference between DeepCrawl and Lumar?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Same product. DeepCrawl rebranded to Lumar in 2022. Most SEOs still call it DeepCrawl out of habit. The product is unchanged — same crawler, same UI, same enterprise focus." }},
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Does DeepCrawl help with content creation?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "No. DeepCrawl is a pure technical SEO crawler. It does not write content, do keyword research, or track rankings beyond technical health. To produce content and grow organic traffic, pair DeepCrawl with a content engine or use a platform like theStacc that handles content end-to-end." }},
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Does DeepCrawl check Core Web Vitals?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes — DeepCrawl integrates with PageSpeed Insights API to pull Core Web Vitals (LCP, INP, CLS) for every crawled URL. You can set thresholds and get alerted when CWV regresses across a section of your site." }},
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is DeepCrawl worth it in 2026?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "For enterprise sites with 1M+ URLs, dedicated SEO engineers, and JavaScript-heavy architectures: yes — DeepCrawl is the category leader. For everyone else: massive overkill. Screaming Frog ($259/yr), Sitebulb ($420/yr), or done-for-you platforms like theStacc cover 95% of needs at 100× less cost." }}
      ]
    }
  ]
};
