        </div>

        <div class="inline-cta">
          <div class="cta-copy">
            <h4>Don't want a $30k SEO tool you can't justify?</h4>
            <p>theStacc handles audits, content, publishing, GBP, and ranks for the businesses that don't need enterprise tooling. <strong>Try it for $1</strong>, cancel anytime.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cta-action">
            <a href="/checkout/" class="cta-btn-inline">Start $1 trial <span>→</span></a>
            <span class="cta-meta">No annual contract</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 id="performance">Performance — DeepCrawl vs Screaming Frog at scale</h2>
        <p>We ran the same crawl on a 2.3M-URL ecommerce site (JavaScript-rendered product pages) using DeepCrawl Cloud, Screaming Frog (8GB RAM), and Sitebulb. Results:</p>

        <div class="stat-grid">
          <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">2.3M</div><div class="stat-lbl">URLs crawled by DeepCrawl</div></div>
          <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">480k</div><div class="stat-lbl">URLs before Screaming Frog crashed</div></div>
          <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">14 hrs</div><div class="stat-lbl">DeepCrawl total crawl time</div></div>
          <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">100%</div><div class="stat-lbl">JS-rendered pages parsed correctly</div></div>
        </div>

        <h3>Enterprise SEO crawler comparison (2.3M-URL test)</h3>

        <div class="chart-card">
          <div class="chart-head">
